entry.title: [color] Have Widgets inherit the ColorMode of their parents
entry.content:
This CL updates views::Widget to follow the ColorMode of its parent

Widget unless explicitly overridden. In the default case this will

fall back to the ColorMode set on the associated ui::NativeTheme.



This ensures that, barring the override case, all Widgets in a given

hierarchy share the same ColorMode. This helps keep the theme of

the UI hierarchy consistent.



The GetUserColor() interface has been removed from the

ColorProviderSource interface for simplicity (not needed).

anchor-scroll, and therefore can fail if the containing block is

fragmented.

every NGPhysicalAnchorQuery there. It also provides two utility

functions that are better abstracted, so that clients like

anchor-scroll and possibly DevTools (in the future) don't need to

deal with fragmentation details.

and marks it with TODOs and a currently failing test. It will be fixed

by a followup patch.

entry.title: [omnibox][ml] Misc batch execution optimizations and cosmetic changes
entry.content:
- Enables batch model execution by default. This way the potential

performance improvement vs. individual execution can be observed

in pre-stable experiment without making the experimentation more

complex.

- If the model is not available or any of the model inputs cannot

be generated from the signals, calls the completion callback with

an empty vector of prediction scores so the ACController can exit

processing the output early.

- Reserves vector capacity and avoids populating them and making

copies where possible.

- Computes `stripped_destination_url` for the eligible matches only.

- Groups only eligible matches for rescoring, reducing the size of

the std::map by half.

- Improves comments and variable names for clarity.

entry.title: Fixed toolbar capture ignoring optional button updates
entry.content:
Toolbar captures are skipped if the toolbar's state hasn't changed. The

container for toolbar state is PhoneCaptureStateToken. This class

keeps a reference to ButtonData, which represents the state of the

optional toolbar button and it uses standard equality checks to

determine of the optional button has changed. This works if the

button is updated with a new instance of ButtonData, but many providers

reuse the same instance, just changing its properties. This results in

button updates (e.g. when changing the button type from settings) not

triggering a new toolbar capture.



This CL updates ButtonData to implement its hashCode() method, this gets

used by PhoneCaptureStateToken to determine if the same instance of

ButtonData changed its attributes.

entry.title: sensors: Reset |last_{raw,rounded}_reading_| when a sensor stops.
entry.content:
Once set, |last_{raw,rounded}_reading_| were never reset, even when a

sensor stopped and the shared buffer was required to be zeroed. This

caused problems for sensors whose reporting mode is ON_CHANGE (which are

the only ones that actually use |last_{raw,rounded}_reading_|) as

starting a sensor again and attempting to set a reading too close to 0

would fail even if it should not.



Fix it by making sure |last_{raw,rounded}_reading_| are reset when an

empty SensorReading is passed, and make the intention more clear by

refactoring the code a bit: move the actual writing to |reading_buffer_|

into a separate function and split UpdateSharedBuffer() into separate

code paths for regular writes and for resetting the buffer.

entry.title: VC UI: Fix a crash when clicking on the stop screen share button.
entry.content:
The crash in the bug attached might be caught because of

ScreenCaptureNotificationUI. In OnStarted, it passes the a stop_callback

to SystemTrayNotifier using base::Unretained. However, since we start to

use this function within the VC tray, the instance of

ScreenCaptureNotificationUI can be deleted before this callback is

triggered (i.e. in ArcScreenCaptureSession the notification can be

deleted, which invalidate the callback). Thus, it is not safe to use

base::Unretained here and we should use a weak pointer.



This is only a quick fix to prevent the crash, a proper fix for stop

screen sharing within VC tray is implemented in b/274956433.

entry.title: [OBC] Warn when secure cookies are allowed access via trustworthy urls
entry.content:
Apply warnings to cookies with a secure source scheme that are being

accessed by a trustworthy, but non-cryptographically secure, url.



This Cl also adds a new warning to cookies which are being created by

a non-cryptographically secure url and specify the `Secure` attribute.

Since trustworthy urls are allowed to set `Secure` cookies we also,

tentatively, set the cookie's source scheme and port to indicate a

secure cookie. This will help prevent confusion about why a given cookie

has a secure source scheme.

If these cookies aren't allowed to be set (because the url actually

isn't trustworthy) then they'll get excluded by the CookieStore/CookieMonster.

Reworks DirectReceiver to use a shared thread-local ipcz node which is

lazily brought up and torn down as needed, rather than a dedicated node

per receiver.



This allows multiple receivers on the same thread to reuse the same node

and therefore the same underlying I/O transports to other nodes.
